name: phenyl_benzoate
source: Aldrich Chemical Company; Aldrich Catalog-Handbook of Fine Chemicals; Milwaukee; WI; 1984.
Reason: 1,2-propanediol base melting point is around 30 degrees Celsius. Two phenyl groups are present, which would significantly increase the melting point due to their ability to enhance π-π interactions and overall molecular rigidity. Each phenyl group may contribute around +30 to +50°C. Additionally, the benzene ring introduces additional rigidity and molecular weight, estimated at around +20°C.
